data.chText: 包，裹（礼物等）
data.enText: to cover sth completely in paper or other material, for example when you are giving it as a present

data.chText: 他花了一个晚上的时间把圣诞礼物都包了起来。
data.enText: He spent the evening wrapping up the Christmas presents.

data.chText: 单块包装的巧克力
data.enText: individually wrapped chocolates

data.chText: 用…包裹（或包扎、覆盖等）
data.enText: to cover sth/sb in material, for example in order to protect it/them

data.chText: 我用毯子把婴儿裹了起来。
data.enText: I wrapped the baby (up) in a blanket.

data.chText: 我用毯子把婴儿裹了起来。
data.enText: I wrapped a blanket around the baby.

data.chText: 把肉用锡箔裹起来后再烹调。
data.enText: Wrap the meat in foil before you cook it.

data.chText: 用…缠绕（或围紧）
data.enText: to put sth firmly around sth/sb

data.chText: 他的脖子上围着一条围巾。
data.enText: A scarf was wrapped around his neck.

data.chText: 他的双臂紧紧环抱她的腰。
data.enText: His arms were wrapped around her waist.

data.chText: （使文字）换行
data.enText: to cause text to be carried over to a new line automatically as you reach the end of the previous line; to be carried over in this way

data.chText: 我怎么才能使文本换行呢？
data.enText: How can I wrap the text around?

data.chText: 如果文本太长，在显示屏放不下的话，会自动换行。
data.enText: The text wraps around if it is too long to fit the screen.

data.enText: to persuade sb to do anything that you want

data.enText: usually used as an order to tell sb to stop talking or causing trouble, etc.

data.chText: （使）穿得暖和
data.enText: to put warm clothes on sb/yourself

data.chText: 她叫他们穿暖和点。
data.enText: She told them to wrap up warm/warmly .
wrap sth↔up

data.chText: 圆满完成，顺利结束（协议或会议等）
data.enText: to complete sth such as an agreement or a meeting in an acceptable way

data.chText: 这就差不多给今天画了个圆满的句号。
data.enText: That just about wraps it up for today.

data.chText: （女用）披肩，围巾
data.enText: a piece of cloth that a woman wears around her shoulders for decoration or to keep warm

data.chText: 包裹（或包装）材料
data.enText: paper, plastic, etc. that is used for wrapping things in

data.chText: 我们备有各种各样的贺卡和礼品包装材料。
data.enText: We stock a wide range of cards and gift wrap .

trans: 圆满完成，圆满结束（工作、协议等）

tr: cloak that is folded or wrapped around a person
the covering (usually paper or cellophane) in which something is wrapped
a sandwich in which the filling is rolled up in a soft tortilla
arrange or fold as a cover or protection
example: wrap the baby before taking her out
roll your hair around your finger
Twine the thread around the spool
She wrapped her arms around the child

tr: crash into so as to coil around
example: The teenager wrapped his car around the fire hydrant

tr: enclose or enfold completely with or as if with a covering

value.def: When you wrap something, you fold paper or cloth tightly round it to cover it completely, for example in order to protect it or so that you can give it to someone as a present.

example.ex: Harry had carefully bought and wrapped presents for Mark to give them...
example.tran: 哈里精心购置了礼物又仔细包好，让马克交给他们。

example.ex: Mexican Indians used to wrap tough meat in leaves from the papaya tree.
example.tran: 墨西哥印第安人过去常用番木瓜树叶把难嚼的肉包起来。

example.ex: Diana is taking the opportunity to wrap up the family presents.
example.tran: 黛安娜利用这个机会将家人的礼物包起来。

value.def: Wrap is the material that something is wrapped in.

example.ex: I tucked some plastic wrap around the sandwiches to keep them from getting stale.
example.tran: 我用塑料包装纸把三明治裹起来，防止变质。

value.def: When you wrap something such as a piece of paper or cloth round another thing, you put it around it.

example.ex: She wrapped a handkerchief around her bleeding palm...
example.tran: 她用手绢将流血的手掌包扎起来。

example.ex: Then she stood up, wrapping her coat around her angrily...
example.tran: 然后她站了起来，怒气冲冲地穿上大衣。

example.ex: Wrap the foil over the fish.

value.def: If someone wraps their arms, fingers, or legs around something, they put them firmly around it.

example.ex: He wrapped his arms around her.

value.tran: 用(手臂、指头或腿)围紧;用…绕住

value.def: A wrap is a piece of clothing which women wear round their shoulders, either to keep them warm when wearing an evening dress, or for decoration over a coat.
If you keep something under wraps, you keep it secret, often until you are ready to announce it at some time in the future.

example.ex: The bids were submitted in May and were meant to have been kept under wraps until October...
example.tran: 标书5月份递交，本欲10月份才予以公布。

example.ex: The date and venue of the game must remain under wraps...
example.tran: 比赛的时间和地点必须保密。

example.ex: You can never keep a launch as big as ours completely under wraps.
example.tran: 像我们这么大规模的新品发布，要绝对保密是不可能的。

value.tran: 保密，秘而不宣（常指待日后宣布）
